{{Unreferenced|date=November 2006}}

In [[informal logic]] and [[argument map]]ping, a '''lemma''' is simultaneously a [[main contention|contention]] for [[premise]]s below it and a premise for a contention above it. [[Transitive relation|Transitivity]]: If one has proof that ''B'' follows from ''A'' and proof that ''C'' follows from ''B'', then one has proof that ''C'' follows from ''A''.

